Jiebing Chen (simplified Chinese: ; traditional Chinese: ; pinyin: Chn Jibng; sometimes credited as Jie-Bing Chen) is a Chinese musician based in the United States specializing in the erhu (two-string fiddle). Born in Shanghai, China, Chen went to the United States in 1989 to study at the State University of New York at Buffalo, where she received an M.A. in music theory. In addition to her work performing Chinese traditional and contemporary music, Chen has also participated in a number of cross-cultural collaborations, including recordings and performances with Vishwa Mohan Bhatt, Bla Fleck, and James Newton. She has also performed jazz with the Jon Jang Sextet and the Beijing Trio (a collaboration with Jang and drummer Max Roach). Her recording Tabula Ras (recorded with Bhatt and Fleck) was nominated for a Grammy Award for Best World Music Album. She lives in California. 
